cz.vutbr.fit.pdb.ateam.adapter

Class DataManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • cz.vutbr.fit.pdb.ateam.adapter.DataManager

  • public class DataManager
extends java.lang.Object
    Class for communicating with the database.

    All database operations needed in the application are included in this class. Class uses singleton pattern and static method getInstance() should be called instead of the constructor.

    Author:
    Tomas Hanus, Tomas Mlynaric, Jakub Tutko

      • saveSpatial

        public boolean saveSpatial(SpatialObjectModel spatialObject)
                    throws DataManagerException
        Method parses all needed data from SpacialObject and builds sql query, which is sent at the server with the createDatabaseUpdate() method.
        Parameters:
        spatialObject - object, which is filled up with all mandatory fields
        Returns:
        id of saveModel model (0 if not successfull, > 0 if ok)
        Throws:
        DataManagerException - when some mandatory field is missing or when exception from createDatabaseUpdate() is received

      • reloadAllSpatialObjects

                             throws DataManagerException
        Method gets all spatial objects saved in the database. Spatial object represents one building at the zoo map.
        Throws:
        DataManagerException - when exception from createDatabaseQuery() is received or when SQLException is caught
